-- Polar Capital assets up 2 pct in March quarter
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 02:23AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 10 (Reuters) - Polar Capital <POLR.L> said group assets under management rose 2 percent to more than $13.2 billion in the March quarter after it took in $750 million in new investment across a range of products.

